			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Fashiolista</strong><br />
Fashiolista is a worldwide community for fashion inspiration. Since our launch in spring 2010, Fashiolista has grown to become one of the leading fashion communities worldwide. With more than 1.5 million members in over 165 countries, we bring fashion inspiration across the globe. Fashiolista is funded by Atomico ventures and several high profile angel investors.</p>
<p>
The team at Fashiolista has a strong technology background and two of the three founders work on product development. The total development team consists of 8 talented people and each of them has a direct impact on the success of the company. We have worked hard to build an excellent development culture, and we encourage creativity and learning. Although we are a small team, we work fast, lean and are able to build amazing stuff together. Scaling a social network is one of the most challenging tasks for developers and devops. Because of the size and activity of the community, there are numerous challenging projects related to scaling and growth.</p>
<p>
Both devops and development at Fashiolista use Python and work closely together. You will be working in a team of experienced developers. We don&#39;t believe in silo&#39;s and development will help you automate systems, come up with simpler architectures and work with you if things hit their limits.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />
You&#39;re core responsibility will be to look after and actively improve our infrastructure. Our infrastructure runs on AWS and is managed by Cloudformation, Puppet and Boto. It will be your responsibility to make improvements, optimizing for speed, maintainability and efficiency (costs). We love to automate, for instance using Puppet, to make everyone&#39;s life easier in the long run. You will also be responsible for putting in place the proper monitoring, logging and failovers for important components of our infrastructure. All of this takes place in an environment where growth in traffic and community size are a constant, so scaling challenges of all shapes and sizes come with the job.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities in short</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Maintaining the Fashiolista application, infrastructure and development tools</li>
<li>
Automating using Python, Boto, Cloudformation and Puppet</li>
<li>
Monitoring for limits and slowdowns to identify issues before our users find out about them</li>
<li>
Identifying, planning and implementing improvements to the infrastructure, with a view to achieving an optimal cost/performance ratio</li>
<li>
Designing new systems in collaboration with the dev team</li>
<li>
Take part in a 24/7 on-call rota</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Who we are looking for</strong><br />
We&rsquo;re looking for someone with strong analytical skills and focus on automation. You need to understand the full web stack and how the components fit together. Since Fashiolista is a large fast and fast growing community, we appreciate hands-ons experience with scaling web and database systems. In addition experience with Django or another Python framework is a big plus.</p>
<p>
<em>Core skills</em></p>
<ul>
<li>
Python coding skills</li>
<li>
Experience running applications on AWS</li>
<li>
Ubuntu/Linux system administration</li>
<li>
PostgreSQL (streaming replication, hot-standby cluster, SQL optimization)</li>
<li>
Puppet</li>
</ul>
<p>
<em>Bonus points for experience with:</em></p>
<ul>
<li>
Cloudformation</li>
<li>
Redis</li>
<li>
SOLR</li>
<li>
RabbitMQ</li>
<li>
Celery</li>
<li>
Vagrant</li>
<li>
Monitoring (Nagios, Munin, Cacti, DataDog, Newrelic)</li>
<li>
Centralized logging, Syslog, Rsyslog, Splunk, PaperTrail</li>
<li>
CS degree</li>
</ul>
<p>
For this position you need to be willing to work in The Netherlands/Amsterdam. Furthermore the position is full time.</p>
<p>
<strong>To conclude</strong><br />
We are looking for someone with a positive work attitude and continuous drive to learn &amp; improve. It doesn&#39;t matter if you are a cum laude graduate, or university drop out, as long as you&rsquo;re extremely passionate about what you do. You will be working in a start-up and we expect your input on a wide range of challenges.</p>
]]></description>
