			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Fashiolista</strong></p>
<p>
Fashiolista is a worldwide community for fashion inspiration. Since our launch in spring 2010, Fashiolista has grown to become one of the leading fashion communities worldwide. With more than 1.6 million members in over 165 countries, we bring fashion inspiration across the globe.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />
You&#39;ll be part of a strong multi-disciplinary team of online professionals. As a manager of the Brand Development department it will be your responsibility to plan and coordinate strategic partnerships with online influencers. These partnerships are a must to keep the Fashiolista brand develop into the right audience, which are the key influencers online. In this position you will be responsible creating and developing creative integrated digital campaigns and various creative collaborations between Fashiolista, brands and other 3rd parties. You will work closely with the Brand Relations team to make all run smoothly, and create tailor-made concepts for brands that generate online exposure. You will be in the lead of the Friends of Fashiolista influencer network, to find new and effective ways to drive relevant traffic towards influencers. As well as vice versa, to make the community grow.</p>
<p>
Daily tasks:<br />
- Keeping direct contact with international fashion bloggers and other online influencers.<br />
- Plan and coordinate creative collaborations online.<br />
- Create and execute online marketing campaigns between Fashiolista and brands like MANGO, Nike, Philips, Sony, Shopbop, COS and many more. All in teamwork with the Sales team of Fashiolista.<br />
- Travel to various fashion weeks and events over the globe to keep in close contact with influencers, brands and everything else fashion related.</p>
<p>
The position is a full-time traineeship, joining the 20+ team in our Amsterdam office, located on the canals. You need to be located in Netherlands (preferebly Amsterdam area) to apply for this position.</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
In depth understanding of the online fashion world.</li>
<li>
Strong attention to detail, organized and good project management skills.</li>
<li>
Interested and/or experienced within the world of fashion bloggers, influencers and social networks.</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills, creative thinker, immune to stress and a team player.</li>
<li>
Very strong English language skills, other languages are a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Why you will love working at Fashiolista</strong><br />
&bull; Young team, startup culture<br />
&bull; Fast growing, many opportunities to develop and learn<br />
&bull; High level of independence to build your own success, entrepreneurial spirit</p>
]]></description>
